    <note>Zong(1) Ying [1718] Ze's son [3897]. Affinal relation of Chen(1) Liang [3075]. A careful search of the collected papers of Chen(1) Liang and Zong(1) Ze will lead to a fairly comprehensive reconstruction of the Wuzhou(b) gentry lineages. For example, see the funerary inscription of Liang's father-in-law, He(2) Hui [3338], whose son He(2) Dabian [3341] was the son-in-law of Zong(1) Wu [3898], the grandson of Ze's brother and whose daughter, He(2) Shi, was the wife of Zong(1) Wu's son, Kai [3896]. It is important to note that the Zong(1), Chen(1) and He(2) lineages were long time Wuzhou(b) residents with little claim to distinction before Zong(1) Ze and Chen(1) Liang became famous. Chen Liang, WJ, 27.2b, 28.1a; XNYL, 63.18a, 112.1a; SS, 360.11a; Zong Ze, WJ, 3.7a-12a. CBD, 2, 1295-6.</note>
